This paper discusses the communication infrastructure and protocols for Advanced Metering Infrastructure (AMI) in the smart grid, which involves networking and communication technologies. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also evaluates the performance of two routing protocols, which involves analyzing the efficiency and effectiveness of the protocols, making cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) and cs.SY (Systems and Control) likely categories as well. Additionally, the paper involves the implementation of an extension version of a routing protocol, which involves software development and programming, making cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) a possible category. Finally, the paper discusses the use of IPv6 and ITU-T recommendations, which involves information technology and standards, making cs.IT (Information Theory) a possible category as well.
